      <title>Solar Power in Central Europe</title>
      <link>https://www.ivankovic.me/marko/blog/smart-home-solar-power/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 05 Sep 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.ivankovic.me/marko/blog/smart-home-solar-power/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;solar-potential&#34;&gt;Solar potential&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My house has excellent solar potential. Itâ€™s roughly on 47 degrees north. One entire side of the&#xA;roof has an azimuth of about 220 degrees and a declination of 31 degrees. The total usable surface&#xA;for the panels is 62 square meters.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The roof is big enough for 36 panels. 24 at a declination of 31 degrees and 12 at 10 degrees. With&#xA;330 wP panels this sums up to 11.8 kWp. The local utility company that installed the system projects&#xA;a yearly production of 12.2 MWh.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
